table.name: time_zone_leap_second
table.Comment: Leap seconds information for time zones

column.name: default_value
column.DefaultExpression: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4'io_block_read_cost' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4'memory_block_read_cost' then 0.25 else NULL end)

column.name: source_uuid
column.Comment: uuid of the source where the transaction was originally executed.

column.name: Channel_name
column.Comment: The replication channel name that connects source and replica.

column.name: Host
column.Comment: The source hostname that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure.

column.name: Port
column.Comment: The source port that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure.

column.name: Network_namespace
column.Comment: The source network namespace that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure. If its value is empty, connections use the default (global) namespace.

column.name: Weight
column.Comment: The order in which the replica shall try to switch the connection over to when there are failures. Weight can be set to a number between 1 and 100, where 100 is the highest weight and 1 the lowest.

column.name: Managed_name
column.Comment: The name of the group which this server belongs to.

column.name: Channel_name
column.Comment: The replication channel name that connects source and replica.

column.name: Managed_name
column.Comment: The name of the source which needs to be managed.

column.name: Configuration
column.Comment: The data to help manage group. For Managed_type = GroupReplication, Configuration value should contain {"Primary_weight": 80, "Secondary_weight": 60}, so that it assigns weight=80 to PRIMARY of the group, and weight=60 for rest of the members in mysql.replication_asynchronous_connection_failover table.

column.name: version
column.Comment: The version of the configuration name.

column.name: event
column.Comment: The event that will trigger the action.

column.name: priority
column.Comment: The order on which the action will be run, value between 1 and 100, lower values first.

column.name: error_handling
column.Comment: On errors during the action will be handled: IGNORE, CRITICAL.

column.name: default_value
column.DefaultExpression: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4'disk_temptable_create_cost' then 20.0 when _utf8mb4'disk_temptable_row_cost' then 0.5 when _utf8mb4'key_compare_cost' then 0.05 when _utf8mb4'memory_temptable_create_cost' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4'memory_temptable_row_cost' then 0.1 when _utf8mb4'row_evaluate_cost' then 0.1 else NULL end)

column.name: Number_of_lines
column.Comment: Number of lines in the file.

column.name: Master_log_name
column.Comment: The name of the master binary log currently being read from the master.

column.name: Master_log_pos
column.Comment: The master log position of the last read event.

column.name: Host
column.Comment: The host name of the source.

column.name: User_name
column.Comment: The user name used to connect to the master.

column.name: User_password
column.Comment: The password used to connect to the master.

column.name: Port
column.Comment: The network port used to connect to the master.

column.name: Connect_retry
column.Comment: The period (in seconds) that the slave will wait before trying to reconnect to the master.

column.name: Enabled_ssl
column.Comment: Indicates whether the server supports SSL connections.

column.name: Ssl_ca
column.Comment: The file used for the Certificate Authority (CA) certificate.

column.name: Ssl_capath
column.Comment: The path to the Certificate Authority (CA) certificates.

column.name: Ssl_cert
column.Comment: The name of the SSL certificate file.

column.name: Ssl_cipher
column.Comment: The name of the cipher in use for the SSL connection.

column.name: Ssl_key
column.Comment: The name of the SSL key file.

column.name: Ssl_verify_server_cert
column.Comment: Whether to verify the server certificate.

column.name: Bind
column.Comment: Displays which interface is employed when connecting to the MySQL server

column.name: Ignored_server_ids
column.Comment: The number of server IDs to be ignored, followed by the actual server IDs

column.name: Retry_count
column.Comment: Number of reconnect attempts, to the master, before giving up.

column.name: Ssl_crl
column.Comment: The file used for the Certificate Revocation List (CRL)

column.name: Ssl_crlpath
column.Comment: The path used for Certificate Revocation List (CRL) files

column.name: Enabled_auto_position
column.Comment: Indicates whether GTIDs will be used to retrieve events from the master.

column.name: Channel_name
column.Comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication

column.name: Public_key_path
column.Comment: The file containing public key of master server.

column.name: Get_public_key
column.Comment: Preference to get public key from master.

column.name: Network_namespace
column.Comment: Network namespace used for communication with the master server.

column.name: Master_compression_algorithm
column.Comment: Compression algorithm supported for data transfer between source and replica.

column.name: Master_zstd_compression_level
column.Comment: Compression level associated with zstd compression algorithm.

column.name: Tls_ciphersuites
column.Comment: Ciphersuites used for TLS 1.3 communication with the master server.

column.name: Source_connection_auto_failover
column.Comment: Indicates whether the channel connection failover is enabled.

column.name: Gtid_only
column.Comment: Indicates if this channel only uses GTIDs and does not persist positions.

column.name: Number_of_lines
column.Comment: Number of lines in the file or rows in the table. Used to version table definitions.

column.name: Relay_log_name
column.Comment: The name of the current relay log file.

column.name: Relay_log_pos
column.Comment: The relay log position of the last executed event.

column.name: Master_log_name
column.Comment: The name of the master binary log file from which the events in the relay log file were read.

column.name: Master_log_pos
column.Comment: The master log position of the last executed event.

column.name: Sql_delay
column.Comment: The number of seconds that the slave must lag behind the master.

column.name: Id
column.Comment: Internal Id that uniquely identifies this record.

column.name: Channel_name
column.Comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication

column.name: Require_row_format
column.Comment: Indicates whether the channel shall only accept row based events.

column.name: Require_table_primary_key_check
column.Comment: Indicates what is the channel policy regarding tables without primary keys on create and alter table queries

column.name: Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_type
column.Comment: Indicates whether the channel will generate a new GTID for anonymous transactions. OFF means that anonymous transactions will remain anonymous. LOCAL means that anonymous transactions will be assigned a newly generated GTID based on server_uuid. UUID indicates that anonymous transactions will be assigned a newly generated GTID based on Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_value

column.name: Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_value
column.Comment: Indicates the UUID used while generating GTIDs for anonymous transactions

column.name: Channel_name
column.Comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication
